      "content": "I hear you, but it's not that simple. Warfarin is a carefully calibrated medication, and your body responds to it in a very specific way. High doses of garlic can indeed have blood-thinning effects, but it's not a controlled or predictable way to manage your condition. The risks of uncontrolled bleeding and other complications far outweigh any potential benefits. I strongly advise against trying to replace warfarin with garlic and smoothies. Stick with your prescribed treatment plan, and if you have concerns, discuss them with your doctor. Your health and safety are the most important things.",
